<Link id="l01123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1123"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1124"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Helper class for calculating the default number of inline elements for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1125"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#96;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&#96;.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1126"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1127"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This should be migrated to a constexpr function when our minimum</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1128"><Highlight kind="comment">/// compiler support is enough for multi-statement constexpr functions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1129" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> T&gt; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements">CalculateSmallVectorDefaultInlinedElements</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1130"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Parameter controlling the default number of inlined elements</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1131"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// for &#96;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&#96;.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1132"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1133"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The default number of inlined elements ensures that</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 1 There is at least one inlined element.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 2 &#96;sizeof(SmallVector&lt;T&gt;) &lt;= kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof&#96; unless</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// it contradicts 1</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a322876b665b12084a3401951797b440e"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">constexpr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a322876b665b12084a3401951797b440e">kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof</a> = 64;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// static&#95;assert that sizeof(T) is not &quot;too big&quot;.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1140"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Because our policy guarantees at least one inlined element, it is possible</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// for an arbitrarily large inlined element to allocate an arbitrarily large</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// amount of inline storage. We generally consider it an antipattern for a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1144"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// SmallVector to allocate an excessive amount of inline storage, so we want</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1145"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// to call attention to these cases and make sure that users are making an</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1146"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// intentional decision if they request a lot of inline storage.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1147"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1148"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We want this assertion to trigger in pathological cases, but otherwise</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1149"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// not be too easy to hit. To accomplish that, the cutoff is actually somewhat</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1150"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// larger than kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof (otherwise,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1151"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#96;SmallVector&lt;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&gt;&#96; would be one easy way to trip it, and that</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1152"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// pattern seems useful in practice).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1153"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1154"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// One wrinkle is that this assertion is in theory non-portable, since</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1155"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// sizeof(T) is in general platform-dependent. However, we don&#39;t expect this</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1156"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// to be much of an issue, because most LLVM development happens on 64-bit</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1157"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// hosts, and therefore sizeof(T) is expected to &#42;decrease&#42; when compiled for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1158"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 32-bit hosts, dodging the issue. The reverse situation, where development</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1159"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// happens on a 32-bit host and then fails due to sizeof(T) &#42;increasing&#42; on a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1160"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 64-bit host, is expected to be very rare.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1161"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static&#95;assert</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1162"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">sizeof</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a>) &lt;= 256,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1163"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;You are trying to use a default number of inlined elements for &quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1164"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;&#96;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&#96; but &#96;sizeof(T)&#96; is really big! Please use an &quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1165"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;explicit number of inlined elements with &#96;SmallVector&lt;T, N&gt;&#96; to make &quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1166"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;sure you really want that much inline storage.&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1167"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1168"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Discount the size of the header itself when calculating the maximum inline</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1169"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// bytes.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1170" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#adebf52e29c244776b4747cb57ec94290"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">constexpr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#adebf52e29c244776b4747cb57ec94290">PreferredInlineBytes</a> =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1171"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a322876b665b12084a3401951797b440e">kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof</a> - </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">sizeof</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;T, 0&gt;</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1172" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">constexpr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3">NumElementsThatFit</a> = <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#adebf52e29c244776b4747cb57ec94290">PreferredInlineBytes</a> / </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">sizeof</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1173" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a737320006b419bc7865600d50e558017"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">constexpr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a737320006b419bc7865600d50e558017">value</a> =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1174"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3">NumElementsThatFit</a> == 0 ? 1 : <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3">NumElementsThatFit</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1175"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1176"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1177"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is a &#39;vector&#39; (really, a variable-sized array), optimized</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1178"><Highlight kind="comment">/// for the case when the array is small.  It contains some number of elements</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1179"><Highlight kind="comment">/// in-place, which allows it to avoid heap allocation when the actual number of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1180"><Highlight kind="comment">/// elements is below that threshold.  This allows normal &quot;small&quot; cases to be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1181"><Highlight kind="comment">/// fast without losing generality for large inputs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1182"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1183"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\note</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1184"><Highlight kind="comment">/// In the absence of a well-motivated choice for the number of inlined</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1185"><Highlight kind="comment">/// elements \\p N, it is recommended to use \\c SmallVector&lt;T&gt; (that is,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1186"><Highlight kind="comment">/// omitting the \\p N). This will choose a default number of inlined elements</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1187"><Highlight kind="comment">/// reasonable for allocation on the stack (for example, trying to keep \\c</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1188"><Highlight kind="comment">/// sizeof(SmallVector&lt;T&gt;) around 64 bytes).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1189"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1190"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\warning This does not attempt to be exception safe.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1191"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1192"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\see https://llvm.org/docs/ProgrammersManual.html#llvm-adt-smallvector-h</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1193"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a>,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1194"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/regcomp-c/#a0240ac851181b84ac374872dc5434ee4">N</a> = <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a737320006b419bc7865600d50e558017">CalculateSmallVectorDefaultInlinedElements&lt;T&gt;::value</a>&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
